# Coding Style

## Language & Build

- **C++17** strict. No C++20 features.
- **Header-only**: all template implementations live in `.hpp` files (out-of-class definitions below the class declaration).
- Short one-liner methods may be defined inline in the class body.

## Naming

- **Namespace**: all code lives under the library namespace (e.g. `MadCart::`, `MadVoro::`, `MeshDecomposer3D::`). Sub-namespaces for subsystems (e.g. `MadVoro::IO::`, `MadVoro::Exception::`).
- **Classes/Structs**: `CamelCase` (e.g. `CartesianMesh3D`, `Face3D`).
- **Methods**: `CamelCase` matching the RICH `Tessellation3D` API where applicable (e.g. `GetPointNo`, `GetCellFaces`, `GetMeshPoint`).
- **Private members**: trailing underscore (`nx_`, `lower_`, `face_neighbors_`).
- **Template parameter**: `PointT` for the 3D point type (must have `.x`, `.y`, `.z` public members).

## Formatting

- 4-space indentation, no tabs.
- Opening brace on **same line** for functions and control flow; **next line** for class/struct/namespace bodies.
- `const T &param` style (space before `&`).
- Section dividers: `// ---- Section Name ----`.

## Header Guards & Includes

- Traditional `#ifndef` / `#define` guards, format: `LIBNAME_FILENAME_HPP` (e.g. `MADCART_CARTESIAN_MESH_3D_HPP`). No `#pragma once`.
- Include order: (1) standard library (alphabetical), (2) third-party (boost, MPI), (3) local project headers.

## Dependencies & Portability

- Core engine must **not** include RICH-specific headers. Keep the library standalone-capable.
- Use `boost::container::small_vector` and `flat_map` for topology containers (`face_vec`, `point_vec`, `AllPointsMap`), defined in `types.hpp`.
- MPI-dependent code is guarded with `#ifdef RICH_MPI`.

## Architecture

- **Engine** (inside submodule): generic, templated on `PointT`, no RICH coupling.
- **Adapter** (outside submodule, in RICH): thin wrapper inheriting `Tessellation3D`, delegates to engine. Lives at `source/3D/tessellation/<Name>.hpp`.
- **Standalone build**: `CMakeLists.txt` detects `CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR == CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR`; provides `install_deps.sh` for external deps.

## Error Handling

- Library-specific exception class (e.g. `MadCartError`, `MadVoroException`) inheriting `std::runtime_error`.
- Use `addEntry(name, value)` for structured error context.
